The paper deals with graph theory, specifically spectral graph theory and sparsification. The results involve eigenvalues of matrices, Laplacian matrices, and graph properties such as girth and average degree. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
